article.headline: Valparaiso 69, IUPUI 55
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Samuel Haanpaa scored 19 points -- 15 of them on 3-pointers -- as Valparaiso beat IUPUI 69-55 on Saturday night. Brandon McPherson had 13 points and four assists for the Crusaders (7-10, 2-2 Mid-Continent Conference), whose widest lead was by 17 with 2:37 left in the game. Haanpaa grabbed seven rebounds and shot 5-of-7 from beyond the arc. Urule Igbavboa added 12 points for Valpo, whose widest lead was by 17 with 2:37 left in the game. The Jaguars (7-9, 1-2) led 32-28 at halftime after stretching the margin to six with 5:13 left in the first half. IUPUI outshot the Crusaders from the field 44 percent to 33.3 percent before the break, but the Jaguars' shooting cooled to 33.3 percent in the second half while Valparaiso's heated up to 66.7 percent. Gary Patterson led the Jaguars with 17 points, including 4-of-7 3-pointers. David Barlow scored 13 for IUPUI, which lagged Valpo 24-12 in the paint.
